      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "Wind slabs can be released by a single winter sport participant in some cases, this also applies at a distance from ridgelines, caution is to be exercised on very steep slopes at transitions from a shallow to a deep snowpack, when entering gullies and bowls for example. <br/> Where the wind was less strong, soft, but not very visible, slabs formed. Shooting cracks when stepping on the snowpack can indicate the danger. <br/> In isolated cases the dry avalanches can be released in deep layers of the snowpack and reach medium size. <br/> <br/> As a consequence of warming and solar radiation, the natural avalanche activity will gradually increase, in particular on extremely steep sunny slopes. As the day progresses, a few natural avalanches are possible. This also applies at the base of rock walls.",
